The paper discusses the signal-space approach for multiplexing multiple data symbols using a single-radio switched antenna, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), radio frequency (cs.RF), system and control (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and communication (cs.COMM). The paper proposes a new approach that overcomes the limitations of previous single-feed MIMO techniques, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in these sub-categories.
